[2] Ukraine
Date: Tue 27 Mar 2018 13:49
Source: Ukrinform [edited]
https://www.ukrinform.net/rubric-emergencies/2429980-health-ministry-over-700-people-fell-ill-with-measles-over-past-week.html


A total of 712 people have fallen ill with measles in Ukraine over the past week [week of Sun 18 Mar 2018], the Health Ministry's press service reports.

"According to the data provided by the Public Health Center of the Health Ministry of Ukraine, 712 people fell ill over the 12th week of 2018: 283 adults and 429 children. Some 8434 people fell ill with measles over 1st 12 weeks of 2018: 2956 adults and 5478 children," reads the report.

In addition, 7 people have died of complications from measles: 5 children and 2 adults.

The largest number of cases of measles was recorded in Ivano-Frankivsk (1760), Zakarpattia (1513), Odesa (1139), Chernivtsi (800), and Lviv (756) regions. The smallest number of number of cases of measles was recorded in Luhansk (4), Sumy (5), Kharkiv (11), and Kherson (13) regions.

