[5] Australia (Queensland): alert
Date: Tue 27 Mar 2018 11:24AM
Source: News [edited]
http://www.news.com.au/national/queensland/measles-case-diagnosed-in-man-who-commuted-on-brisbane-rail-network-on-march-19-and-20/news-story/4eb97d66632742fddc96bb8b8cabc18d


A Brisbane man has been diagnosed with the highly infectious measles virus in the 4th case recorded in Queensland this year [2018].

The Metro North Public Health Unit said the man had travelled on public transport on 19 and 20 Mar [2018] while he unknowingly had the virus.

Public health physician James Smith [listed the locations where people should be alert for measles symptoms. - see URL above]

Measles complications can include pneumonia and encephalitis, inflammation of the brain, which can be life threatening.

Dr Smith said measles was one of the most infectious of all communicable diseases and was spread by tiny droplets generated by coughing and sneezing.

[Byline: Janelle Miles]

